<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   FYROM's Gligorov Warns of `Danger' of Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503123894 Hamburg DPA in German 1132 GMT 15 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1503123894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov on 
Tuesday [15 March] in Bonn described the Greek embargo against 
his country as a danger to the stability in the entire region. 
Gligorov, who along with Slovene President Milan Kucan was 
invited to a Europe Dialogue Forum sponsored by Bundestag 
President Rita Suessmuth, underlined his readiness for immediate 
talks with the participation of UN mediator Cyrus Vance. 
  For two years, Greece has been trying "irrationally and 
emotionally" to prevent international recognition of The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM]. The Macedonian 
president once more denied any territorial claims on the Greek 
province of the same name and emphasized the need for a peaceful 
agreement. "Our objective is the Europeanization of the 
Balkans," Gligorov said. 
  Slovene President Kucan, who had come on a private visit to 
Bonn just like Gligorov, said that implementing the market 
economy and full integration into Europe was his supreme 
objective. Both presidents were planning to pay a courtesy call 
on Federal President Richard von Weizsaecker on Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

