<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Biblis Nuclear Power Plant To Reopen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503182494 Hamburg DPA in German 1630 GMT 15 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1503182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Wiesbaden -- Reactor block A of the Biblis nuclear 
power plant in Hesse will start operating again. By agreeing to 
this decision, Hesse Environment Minister Joschka Fischer 
(Alliance 90/Greens) gave in in the dispute with Federal 
Environment Minister Klaus Toepfer (Christian Democratic Union). 
  The ministry in Wiesbaden stated that the decree issued 11 
days ago after a fire in the reactor can be lifted. According 
to the decree, preparations for a renewed operation of the 
reactor had to be stopped after the regular revision. 
  It was also announced that the evaluation of the expert 
reports commissioned by Fischer and Toepfer, which came to 
different conclusions, did not reveal any findings that would 
have required a closure of the plant. 

</TEXT>

