<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tirol Officials Resign in Election Aftermath </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603114794 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 16 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1603114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Tirol's SPOe Leaders Resign"] </F>
  [Excerpt] On Tuesday afternoon [15 March] Hans Tanzer, 
chairman of the Tirolean Social Democratic Party [SPOe] and 
deputy provincial governor, announced his resignation during a 
meeting of the SPOe Diet group in Innsbruck. In the morning 
Walter Hengl, the second SPOe member of the Tirolean Government 
and provincial councilor for health and social matters, had 
already announced his departure from politics and had suggested 
Nationalrat deputy Walter Guggenberger as his successor. 
  Tanzer resigned from all his posts during the meeting. 
  Regarding a successor for Tanzer, the vote taken in the diet 
group between Provincial Party Secretary Herbert Prock and 
Nationalrat Deputy Walter Guggenberger led to a stalemate with 
both receiving seven votes. A definitive decision is to be made 
by the Provincial Party Executive Committee during a meeting on 
Monday evening. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

