<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ruehe Says Bundeswehr Needs Crisis Forces </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503132394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1210 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1503132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- In light of altered international 
conditions, the Bundeswehr should expand its ability to take 
part in the resolution of international crises. The armed 
forces are least prepared for these tasks at present, Federal 
Defense Minister Volker Ruehe said today after the cabinet 
approved the Bundeswehr 1994 White Paper in Bonn. 
  Germany needs a minimum contigent "of available, quickly 
deployable and transferable crisis reaction forces with a high 
degree of professionalism," which were capable of multinational 
cooperation. 
  At the same time the armed forces for national defense 
should 
be "scaled down both in numbers and in their readiness for 
deployment and be made more responsive to mobilization." 
According to Ruehe, nothing will be changed with regard to 
conscription. It remains a constituent element of the 
Bundeswehr. 

</TEXT>

