<H3> <TI>   Defense Budget Escapes Control Constraints </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1503132194 Paris LIBERATION in French 15 Mar 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> BR1503132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LIBERATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "D.Gd": "Defense Escapes Budget Constraints"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Defense Minister Francois Leotard obtained 
confirmation from the Budget Ministry: The Defense Ministry's 
1995-2000 military program law will provide for an annual 
increase of 0.5 percent in equipment expenditure. For the armed 
forces and the Ministry, which initially requested an increase 
of 3 to 5 percent on the basis of the 100.4-billion-franc 
spending obligated in the 1994 budget, this certainly is no 
great prize. However, with this pledged increase over the next 
few years, the defense budget actually constitutes an exception 
to the multiyear Law on Public Expenditure Control, which 
stipulates a 0.5-percent decrease in all state budgets. 
Initially, the Budget Ministry had requested that equipment 
spending in the miliatary program law be reduced by 1 percent 
instead of 0.5 percent. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

