<H3> <TI>   Ciller Says Nevruz To Be National Holiday </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1503070694 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0530 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1503070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] Prime Minister Tansu Ciller 
held a question-and-answer dinner meeting with reporters at the 
prime minister's residence last night. 
  In answer to a question on what will happen during Nevruz, 
Ciller said: I do not think anything will happen during Nevruz. 
If we could die together during the War of Independence, we can 
also celebrate the holiday together in order to protect the 
undivided integrity and independence of this country. 
  Ciller further noted: I will make Nevruz a national holiday. 
Nevruz will be the holiday of all of Turkey. We will enter 1995 
with Nevruz as an official holiday. We will celebrate Nevruz 
together. If we could die together, then we can also celebrate 
holidays together. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

