<H3> <TI>   Liberal Forum To Challenge Salzburg Election </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603114894 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 16 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1603114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Schmidt Will Challenge Elections"] </F>
  [Text] The Liberal Forum (LF) is to challenge the diet 
elections held in Salzburg last Sunday [13 March]. This was 
announced by Federal Spokeswoman Heide Schmidt at a press 
conference in Vienna on Tuesday. 
  She justified this step by pointing out that the principle 
of 
proportional representation, which is set down in the 
Constitution, has been violated. Schmidt thinks the fact that 
in Salzburg about 10 percent of the votes in one constituency 
are required for a basic mandate and thus for entering the diet 
is a distortion of democracy. The LF will challenge the election 
results in Salzburg and, demonstratively, also in the provinces 
of Styria and Carinthia, where there are similarly high 
thresholds. 
  In addition to contesting the elections in the 
Constitutional 
Court, the LF will also petition the Austrian Government to 
challenge the election laws in those provinces where the 
principle of proportional representation is violated. Schmidt 
stressed that her party had already announced its intention to 
challenge the elections before election day and would have done 
so even if it had entered the Diet. 
  Regardless of this challenge, the LF also opposes the way in 
which declarations of support must be presented for a party to 
be permitted to run in elections. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

