<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Air Links, Bilateral Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603144094 Tehran IRNA in English 1311 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, March, 16, IRNA -- Visiting Iranian Deputy 
Foreign Minister Mahmud Va'ezi and Deputy Minister of Transport 
and Environment Antonio Llardan have discussed ways of speeding 
up the establishment of Madrid-Tehran air link and finalizing a 
surface transport agreement between the two countries. 
  In a meeting held here Tuesday night [15 March], the two 
officials described as "friendly" bilateral relations and 
explored new avenues for expansion of mutual relations in 
various fields. 
  The Spanish official announced Madrid's readiness for 
participating in various Iranian economic projects. 
  Outlining economic and commercial policies of Iran, Va'ezi, 
welcomed Madrid's willingness to help in implementing economic 
projects in Iran. 
  Also on Tuesday, the Iranian official held talks with 
Spanish 
Foreign Ministry Director General Francisco Villar on issues of 
mutual interests as well as regional and international crises. 
  Calling for promotion of Tehran-Madrid cooperation, Villar 
said the full implementation of agreements already reached 
between Iran and Spain could pave the way for expansion of 
bilateral cooperation, particularly in economic area. 
Expressing hope that the second session of Iran-Spain joint 
economic commission would be held in Tehran in a near future, he 
stressed the need for providing further facilities for Spanish 
investors to invest in Iran. 
  Va'ezi announced Iran's readiness to upgrade ties with 
Spain, 
noting that there was no restriction on expansion of bilateral 
cooperation. 
  The two also discussed the crises in Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
Russia, Iraq, Central Asia and the Middle East. 

</TEXT>

