<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Uncover Plot To Kill Anti-Mafia Judges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503145594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1348 GMT 
15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There is to be tighter security around Messina's 
Palace of Justice and for some of the judges who are said to be 
Mafia targets. These were the decisions made by the Committee 
for Order and Security which met in the Messina Prefect's Office. 
  The meeting follows the news that the mafia has made plans 
to 
kill, among others, Judge Antonio Di Pietro. In particular, the 
bosses are said to have set aside 500 million lire for the 
project. The operation was revealed to investigators by the 
supergrass, Luigi Sparacio, whose tesitmony has led to the 
arrest of dozens of people during the last few months. 

</TEXT>

