<F P=100> SWITZERLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bill Tightening Political Asylum Law Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603164794 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 1500 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swiss lower house has followed the Senate in 
giving its backing to a controversial bill to tighten the law on 
political asylum. The house approved giving the police rather 
than a judge the right to decide whether to expel asylum-seekers 
who try to stay in Switzerland illegally, or hold them in 
detention. The new law will come into force in July. The house 
also passed a series of recommendations aimed at boosting 
cooperation and understanding between the different language 
regions in Switzerland. 

</TEXT>

