<H3> <TI>   Parliamentary Relations With Iran Discussed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603204594 Tehran IRNA in English 1938 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1603204594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, March 16, IRNA -- Iran's ambassador to 
Finland, Sayyed 'Ali Mahmoudi, discussed in Helsinki Wednesday 
[16 March] Iran-Finnish parliamentary relations as well as 
international affairs with the new Finish parliament president 
Riitta Uosukainen. 
  During the talks, Uosukainen referring to the importance of 
the Tehran-Helsinki ties stressed the need for a further 
development of bilateral relations, exchange of parlimentary 
delegations, and also parliamentary cooperations. 
  Mahmoudi, expressing his concern with human rights abuses in 
the occupied Palestine and Bosnia-Herzegovina, called on Finland 
to actively support an end to the atrocities. 
  The Finnish politician said: "Five years ago nobody could 
imagine that the world would witness new wars," she also 
informed Mahmoudi on the presence of Finish soldiers in Bosnia. 
  In a separate meeting, also on Wednesday, Mahmoudi held 
talks 
with Perti Pasio, president of Finland's parliamentary Foreign 
Relations Committee, on the establishment of a parliamentary 
friendship group, and exchange of parliamentary delegations. 
  A high ranking Iranian Parliamentary delegation, headed by 
Majlis Vice Speaker Hojatoleslam Dr. Hassan Rowghani, is 
expected to visit Finland in the near future. 

</TEXT>

