<H3> <TI>   Turkish `Agents' Believed Responsible for Bomb at Mosque </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603200294 Nicosia CyBC Television Network in Greek 1830 
GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1603200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CyBC Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Turkish agents could be responsible for the bomb 
explosion last night at a mosque near Faneromeni Church in 
Nicosia. This is the conclusion reached by the investigative 
authorities. Correspondent Yeoryios Platonos has the following 
report: 
  [Begin Platonos recording] The bomb that exploded last night 
on Lefkonos Street was made with a small quantity of high 
density explosive material and was placed on the outside wall of 
the mosque. The homemade device exploded at 2300. The Criminal 
Investigation Department [TAE] is evaluating information that 
Turkish agents are responsible for the explosion. It is 
believed that the Turks possibly came from the occupied areas to 
cause tension in view of the Cyprus issue talks. TAE is also 
studying the relation of this incident to the arrival of the 
Greek National Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis. Police last 
night visited and searched other mosques as a precautionary 
measure. A UN officer visited the area after the explosion, 
possibly after notification by the Turks. The explosion caused 
the shattering of windows of a nearby school and shops. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

