<H3> <TI>   Ministry Demands Protection for Diplomats in Turkey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1703092594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1800 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703092594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Ministry spokesman Konstandinos Bikas made 
the following statement today: 
  Based on existing practice and on relevant Turkish requests, 
the government has taken all the necessary measures aimed at 
offering not ordinary, but increased protection for the Turkish 
Embassy and consular staff in our country. The Turkish side has 
expressed its satisfaction with this. 
  But you cannot say the same thing about the protection the 
Turkish side is offering our staff who serve in Turkey, because 
recently, unidentified people have not only harassed and 
threatened these staff, in word and deed, but they have even 
targeted their family members. The Turkish side's attention is 
drawn to the repercussions that similar actions might have, for 
which Ankara would be responsible. 
  It is demanded that every measure be adopted to end the 
harassment and protect our official staff and their families in 
Turkey. 
  All of the above was stressed in relevant representations 
made to the Turkish Foreign Ministry and to the Turkish Embassy 
here, the Foreign Ministry spokesman's statement concludes. 

</TEXT>

