<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Athens To Veto FYROM Inclusion in EU Restructuring Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1603171994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1600 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1603171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said that 
Greece will veto The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
[FYROM] participation in the European Union's [EU] PHARE 
[Economic Reconstruction Aid for Poland and Hungary] program, 
which provides financing for the economic restructuring of 
Central and East European countries. FYROM's participation in 
the program was announced by the EU Commission's legal 
department, but as Venizelos explained, the extension of the 
program to countries of the former Yugoslavia is decided by the 
EU Council of Ministers where agreement is necessary. FYROM 
participation in the program requires a special regulation as 
happened in the case of Croatia. 

</TEXT>

