<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister on Objectives of Cyprus Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1503161994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1503161994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Greek National Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis 
said that the objective of his visit to Cyprus, which will begin 
tomorrow, is to promote the coordination of defense plans 
between Greece and Cyprus. In a statement, Arsenis also said 
that the coordination is necessary because the two countries 
face a common danger. The Greek national defense minister noted 
that a prerequisite for the coordination of defense plans is the 
coordination of armaments programs. That is why, during his 
visit, he will be accompanied by the president and other 
officials of the greek arms industry. Asked why a common 
defense goal had not been promoted in the past, Arsenis said 
that perhaps in the past there was too much optimism about the 
initiatives for a diplomatic solution. In order to promote a 
diplomatic, political, and viable solution, Arsenis stressed 
that we should have high credibility in the area of defense. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

