<H3> <TI>   * Possible Candidate for Succession </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20472B </F>
<F P=103> 94P20472B </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] Given the "notoriously tense" relations 
between Minister of Foreign Affairs Karolos Papoulias and 
alternate Minister of Foreign Affairs Theodhoros Pangalos, the 
13 February Athens daily I KATHIMERINI questions whether the 
latter will remain in place after Greece's term as European 
Union president ends. The newspaper cites diplomats "in the 
know" as saying that Pangalos will probably move to another 
ministry. Meanwhile, other sources maintain that the alternate 
minister will definitely not seek an appointment as European 
Union commissioner, as was rumored late last year. According to 
the newspaper, this means that the list of possible successors 
to Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou would grow by yet another 
strong candidate. 

</TEXT>

