<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chancellor Announces Decline in Unemployment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603130694 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 16 Mar 94 p 17 </F>
<F P=103> AU1603130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "chs": "13,000 Unemployed Less Than a Year </F>
Ago"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- According to Chancellor Franz Vranitzky, 
the Austrian economy is moving upward again. A sign of an 
"economic revival" is a "reversal of the trend" in the labor 
market. At the moment 13,000 more persons are employed than in 
mid-March 1993. 
  As Vranitzky said yesterday at a press conference after the 
Cabinet meeting, unemployment went down by 25,000 persons over 
the past two weeks. For men, who had been particularly affected 
by job cuts in industry, unemployment is 8.5 percent below the 
value of March 1993, Vranitzky said. A total of 32,000 
foreigners currently are unemployed, compared with 38,000 at the 
end of February. Vranitzky stated that the more favorable 
development is due to the fact that construction work began 
earlier this year. He expects the latest development to have a 
positive effect on the referendum for membership in the European 
Union. 

</TEXT>

