<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- The halt on the deportation of Bosnian 
refugees from Germany has been extended by six months to 30 
September. A spokesman of the Interior Ministry confirmed in 
Bonn today that the interior ministers of the laender have 
agreed on this measure. Without this decision, the ban would 
have expired by the end of this month. The spokesman declined 
to comment on the number of refugees who are currently in 
Germany. 

