<H3> <TI>   Bonn Regrets New Delays in EU Enlargement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603124594 Hamburg DPA in German 1211 GMT 16 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1603124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- On Wednesday [16 March] the Federal 
Government regretted the new delay in the membership 
negotiations. The agreement with Norway on the fishery issue, 
which was achieved over last night, is to be "emphatically 
welcomed," in particular since FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
played a "decisive part" in it, Deputy Government Spokesman 
Norbert Schaefer said. 
  Without mentioning Spain and Britain by name, the Federal 
Government expressly regretted "the attitude of two partners," 
who have once again prevented a restructured blocking minority 
for votes in the larger Union. However, Bonn confidently hopes 
that a final agreement can be achieved at a special meeting next 
Tuesday. 

