<F P=101> Inter-European Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   EC Approves German Funding for Research Program </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1603150494 Brussels RAPID Database in English 16 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1603150494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RAPID Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [EC Document No. DOC/IP/94/211: "Commission Approves the </F>
German Aid Programme `EUREKA-Programme JESSI'"] 
  [Text] The Commission raised no objections to the 
implementation of the German research and development (R and D) 
state aid programme entitled "EUREKA-Programm JESSI [Joint 
European Submicron Silicon Initiative]." 
  The scheme with a budget of 307 mio [million] German marks 
(about 156 mECU) up to 1996 supports basic industrial research. 
  The objective of JESSI consists in creating a know-how and 
research network throughout Europe, in which scientists, 
producer of components and systems user work together in order 
to ensure an European independent position regarding the basic 
technology of microsystems. Beneficiaries are enterprises and 
scientific institutions. 
  The notified intensity of 50 percent gross for basic 
industrial research projects, 60 percent gross for this type of 
research in the former GDR, 60 percent gross for SMEs [small- 
and medium-size enterprises] and 65 percent gross for SMEs 
conducting such research in the former GDR is in accordance with 
the Community framework for state aids for R and D and previous 
decisions by the Commission. 
  The aids for R and D given under the programme 
"EUREKA-Programm JESSI" can be considered to be compatible with 
the common market since they promote the execution of an 
important project of common European interest. They may 
therefore profit from the exemption provided for in Articles 
92(3)(b) of the EC-Treaty and 61(3)(b) of the EEA-Treaty. 

</TEXT>

