<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Says U.S. Nuclear Test Moratorium `Exemplary' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1603154594 Hamburg DPA in German 1522 GMT 16 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1603154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel, of the 
Free Democratic Party of Germany, on Wednesday [16 March] 
praised U.S. President Clinton's decision to extend the 
moratorium on nuclear tests by another year until September 1995 
as exemplary for other nations. It will "significantly 
increase" the chances to achieve an unlimited test ban treaty in 
the Geneva moratorium talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-19496 </DOCNO>
