<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Portugese Minister Moots Idea of Regional Defense Force </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1603142594 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
1200 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1603142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In view of the issue of Islamic fundamentalism, 
southern European countries may set up a new military structure. 
According to Defense Minister Fernando Nogueira, who was 
speaking in Paris, Portugal could participate in this structure. 
It would comprise an air and sea structure tailored to 
Mediterranean needs. The project is already on paper and 
includes Spain, France, and Italy. Daniel Ribeiro reports from 
Paris. 
  [Ribeiro] Military cooperation between southern European 
countries appears to be developing with Portugal's agreement in 
principle regarding the air and sea Mediterranean force which 
includes France, Spain, and Italy. It is a force which will 
cover a strategic area in view of the disruption affecting 
Maghreb countries, especially Algeria where military pressure 
from Islamic fundamentalists is increasing. In addition to 
this, Fernando Nogueira also discussed the situation in Angola, 
Mozambique, and Bosnia-Herzegovina, with his French counterpart. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

