Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Burgenland Provincial Councilor Christa Krammer 
(49) is the new health minister. Shortly after her presentation 
by Chancellor Vranitzky she was sworn in by President Klestil. 
  Krammer is a lawyer. As provincial councilor she was 
responsible for, among other things, the field of preventive 
health care. She told the press conference introducing her that 
she considers all spheres of her ministry (health, consumer 
protection, sports) equal. 
  The Nationalrat is currently holding a debate on the 
government reshuffle. 

