<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bundesrat Approves Government Move to Berlin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803104494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0957 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1803104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The Bundesrat approved the 
so-called Berlin/Bonn law today. The law, which has already 
been passed by the Bundestag, sets out the arrangements for the 
move of the Bundestag and government to Berlin. Under the 
arrangements, the German Government is to move to Berlin "in 
temporal coordination with the Bundestag." At the same time, a 
"fair division of labor" between Berlin and Bonn will be laid 
down by means of the allocation of federal ministries to the two 
cities. Several federal bodies are to move their headquarters 
to Bonn. The region will also receive financial compensation. 
The costs of the move are put at around 20 billion German marks. 

</TEXT>

