<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Willingness To Remove Troops From Golan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703175694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1700 GMT 
17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin, visiting Rome, 
has expressed his willingness in principle to withdraw Israeli 
troops from the Golan Heights within a global framework of 
security and guarantees for the Jewish state. Earlier Rabin was 
received by John Paul II and had met Prime Minister Carlo 
Azeglio Ciampi. 
  Commenting on his meeting with the Pope, Rabin stressed that 
he had not asked the Vatican to take any diplomatic initiatives. 
He added, however, that the Holy See would exert moral pressure 
for the resumption of peace talks. 

</TEXT>

