<H3> <TI>   Latvian Delegation Visit; Ulmanis Meets With Pope </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703173894 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1000 GMT 17 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1703173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Latvian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of the Republic of Latvia, led by State 
President Guntis Ulmanis, is continuing its visit to Italy. At 
1100 today the Latvian president met Pope John Paul II. Also 
this morning the delegation, led by Foreign Minister Georgs 
Andrejevs, met the Vatican secretary of state, Cardinal Angelo 
Sodano. 
  At present, the Latvian president is holding a news 
conference at the Grand Hotel, and later there will be a dinner 
given by Italian industrialists. 

