<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iran's Va'ezi Holds Talks With Spanish Officials </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1703154894 Tehran IRNA in English 1200 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1703154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, March 17, IRNA -- The visiting Iranian 
Deputy Foreign Minister Mahmud Va'ezi discussed promotion of 
Tehran-Madrid ties in separate meetings with Spanish officials 
Wednesday [16 March]. In a meeting with the Spanish Foreign 
Minister Javier Solano, the two sides discussed the latest 
international and regional developments. 
  Promotion of parliamentary cooperation was stressed in 
Va'ezi's meeting with President of the Spanish Senate Juan Jose 
Laborda Martin. The two sides called for expansion of mutual 
ties. 
  Accepting an invitation from the Iranian Majlis Speaker 
Hojjat ol-Eslam 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri, the Spanish official 
expressed hope to visit Tehran at the first opportune time. 
  Meanwhile, Va'ezi discussed mutual economic and industrial 
ties in a meeting with Minister of State for Economic Affairs 
Alfredo Pastor. Voicing his country's willingness to expand 
ties with Tehran, Pastor called for further contribution of 
Spanish institutions to various projects in Iran. 

</TEXT>

