<H3> <TI>   Air Force Interested in JAS-39 Gripen Fighter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1703095194 Oslo AFTENPOSTEN in Norwegian 15 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> BR1703095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo AFTENPOSTEN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Norwegian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "JAS to Meeting in Norway?"] </F>
  [Text] The Norwegian Air Force wants to see the JAS-39 
Gripen multirole air defense and attack aircraft at an air 
display in Norway this summer and has sent a formal request to 
the Swedish Air Force to that effect, Lt. Col. Anders Eisen 
revealed. 
  "Before we can reply, the Air Force and the JAS consortium 
has to fix its next program of test flights," he said. "The 
only thing we can do at the moment is show the aircraft on the 
ground or in a simple fly-past." 
  The JAS received bad press when it crashed during an air 
show 
at the Water Festival last year. 
  According to Jan Ahlgren of Saab's Military Aircraft 
Division, Norway -- which will start replacing its U.S. F-5 
aircraft by the turn of the century -- is among the countries 
which have shown an interest in the JAS-39. 

</TEXT>

