<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Announces 13 Nov for EU Referendum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803100194 Paris AFP in English 0858 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1803100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Stockholm, March 18 (AFP) -- Sweden will hold a 
referendum on joining the European Union (EU) November 13, 
Swedish Prime Minister Carl Bildt announced Friday [18 March] 
after meeting with political party leaders. 
  "Finding a date that makes membership possible by January 1, 
1995 while giving all political parties a chance to campaign and 
spread information about the EU were the decisive factors in 
selecting the date," Bildt said. 
  "Despite the fact that a June referendum would have been the 
most direct and best alternative, I have taken into 
consideration the strong request by the Social Democrats and 
chosen a later date," he added. 
  The Social Democratic opposition had campaigned for a 
November referendum. 

</TEXT>

