<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Polish Defense Minister Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1603072494 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2100 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1603072494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Polish National Defense Minister Piotr 
Kolodziejczyk has arrived in Ankara on an official visit. He 
was received at Esenboga Airport by National Defense Minister 
Mehmet Golhan. 
  In a statement here, Golhan said that relations between 
Turkey and Poland have always been conducted with mutual 
confidence and friendship, even during the Cold War. He said 
Turkey appreciates Poland's efforts to join the Partnership for 
Peace process. Poland is an important country for European 
security, he said, and will make valuable contributions to this 
process. 
  In turn, the Polish defense minister said the warm welcome 
he 
received is a sign of the good relations between the two 
countries. He pointed out that President Suleyman Demirel's 
visit to Poland last November had a positive effect on the 
Polish people's attitude toward Turkey. He added that remarks 
made by President Demirel during the visit also expressed 
Poland's expectations with regard to NATO and European security. 

</TEXT>

