<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ankara Court Arrests Six Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1703142994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1300 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1703142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] At the end of their interrogation at the Ankara 
State Security Alternate Court, five Democracy Party [DEP] 
deputies and one independent who were stripped of their immunity 
were arrested today. 
  Early this morning, the six deputies were taken from the 
Security Directorate to the Ankara State Security Court under 
heavy security. After their files were studied, two judges 
interrogated them. 
  Chief Prosecutor Nusret Demiral later said that Hatip Dicle, 
DEP leader and Diyarbakir deputy, did not make a statement at 
the Alternate Court, which subsequently ruled to arrest Hatip 
Dicle, DEP Diyarbakir Deputy Leyla Zana, DEP Sirnak Deputy Orhan 
Dogan, DEP Mus Deputy Sirri Sakik, DEP Mardin Deputy Ahmet Turk, 
and independent Sirnak Deputy Mahmut Alinak. 
  The prosecutor is demanding that the deputies be tried for 
violating Article 125 of the Turkish Penal Code. The article in 
question envisages the death sentence for treason, and for 
crimes against the sovereignty and indivisible unity of the 
state, country, and nation. 

</TEXT>

