<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mentese: Government `Cannot' Negotiate With PKK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1703160794 Ankara ANATOLIA in Turkish 1510 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1703160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aydin (AA) -- Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has 
said: We cannot damage democracy by sitting at the negotiating 
table with Abdullah Ocalan [leader of the Workers Party of 
Kurdistan]. 
  Speaking at a news conference in Aydin, Mentese noted that 
the backbone of the separatist organization has been broken in 
the struggle waged against terror and added: 
  The government had to take certain measures regarding 
various 
developments in the country. As a matter of fact, we have 
managed to break the backbone of the separatist organization 
through the measures we have taken. 
  The necessary measures have been taken throughout the 
country 
to ensure that the 27 March elections are held in a secure 
atmosphere. These measures are also valid for the Nevruz holiday 
celebrations to be held on 21 March. We are sending some 
150,000 troops to the southeastern Anatolian region to ensure 
security during the elections. 
  Mentese said that the leader of the separatist organization, 
Ocalan, has been exerting efforts beyond belief to sit at the 
negotiating table within a political framework with the Turkish 
Republic in a bid to keep his name and his organization on the 
world agenda and added: He will, however, never be able to 
realize this because we are rejecting this proposal which is 
tantamount to harming democracy. 
  Mentese concluded by saying that a draft bill is being 
prepared that will regulate the passage through the Bosporus of 
tankers carrying dangerous cargo. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-19558 </DOCNO>
