<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economic, Trade Agreement Signed With FYROM </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1703204494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2000 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1703204494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Turkey and The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia [FYROM] have signed in Ankara an agreement regarding 
economic and trade cooperation. 
  The agreement, which was signed by Mehmet Mogultay, labor 
and 
social security minister, and FYROM's Economy Minister Petrus 
Stefanov envisages cooperation between the two countries in the 
areas of transportation, communication, and banking. 

</TEXT>

