<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Republican People's Party Mayoral Candidate Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1703160694 Ankara ANATOLIA in Turkish 1515 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1703160694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, (A.A) -- Muhyettin Ayata, the 
Republican People's Party mayorship candidate for the Kayapinar 
township in Diyarbakir, has been killed following an armed 
attack. Ayata's wife and brother-in-law were also seriously 
wounded in the attack. 
  According to information received from authorities, Ayata, 
his wife, and his brother-in-law were attacked by unidentified 
persons near the Huzurevi neighborhood last night around 2300. 
  Muhyettin Ayata (50) was killed instantly. Rahime Ayata (38) 
and her brother-in-law Abdurrahman Bulbul (29) were taken to the 
Dicle University Faculty of Medicine Hospital for treatment. 
  Efforts are under way to catch the assailants. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

