<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leotard Warns on Possible Reconsideration of Bosnia Role </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1703130094 Paris AFP in English 1238 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1703130094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cambrai, France, March 17 (AFP) -- France on 
Thursday [17 March] warned it might reconsider its participation 
in UN peacekeeping in Bosnia-Herzegovina if its soldiers could 
not "protect themselves" against aggression, the French defense 
minister said. 
  Francois Leotard spoke at a memorial service in honor of a 
French UN soldier killed in northwestern Bosnia last week. 
After the incident, France criticized the United Nations for 
its "lack of resolve" in responding to attacks on UN 
peacekeepers in sensitive Bosnian zones. 
  Leotard warned that the "resolve" of France and its soldiers 
in Bosnia could be sustained "only if our soldiers are, through 
the use of legitimate force, protected against aggression." 
  "We cannot accept that the rule of law is being disarmed and 
that violence is going unpunished," he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

