<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greek Defense Minister Meets With Ministers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1703181994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1703181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Greek National Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis 
met this afternoon with Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis as 
part of his contacts with the Cyprus Government to promote the 
implementation of the unified defense doctrine between Greece 
and Cyprus. In a statement after the meeting, which took place 
at the Foreign Ministry, Foreign Minister Mikhailidhis said that 
Arsenis' visit shows that the political decisions of the Greek 
and Cypriot governments are being implemented. Arsenis did not 
make a statement. 
  This morning the Greek minister of national defense visited 
the National Guard General Staff [YEEF], where with Cypriot 
Defense Minister Konstandinos Iliadhis, he chaired a meeting. 
The meeting was attended by the Greek ambassador, members of 
Arsenis' entourage, the National Guard chief and high-ranking 
officers of the National Guard. Before the meeting at the YEEF, 
Arsenis and Iliadhis had a private meeting. 
  Speaking at the Defense Ministry, Arsenis stressed that the 
joint defense doctrine is not new. He said that it was used 
even by Kimon [ancient Greek general] and this proves that even 
in the days of the trireme Hellenism was projected in the 
creation of Greek wonders. He also said that today, with modern 
means of communications, distance has disappeared and we are 
close, very close. Hellenism's soul, he stressed, is one. 
Arsenis said that serious preparations have been made, and 
expressed the conviction that by the end of the day we will 
achieve everything we desire. 

</TEXT>

