<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dane Appointed To Senior EU Directorate Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1803141294 Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE in Danish 16 Mar 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> BR1803141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Danish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "New Danish EU Boss"] </F>
  [Text] Peter Baumann, the 54-year-old head of department at 
the Agriculture Ministry, has been appointed to head the Danish 
EU [European Union] Directorate, Socialist Prime Minister Poul 
Nyrup Rasmussen announced yesterday. 
  The EU Directorate administers EU funds worth between 11 and 
12 billion kroner each year. Peter Baumann will take up his new 
post on 15 April. He will take charge of 240 employees 
following the recent recruitment of 38 extra staff in the EU 
directorate, among other things with a view to coping with the 
hectare grants. 
  After graduating in law from Copenhagen University in 1965, 
Peter Baumann was a practicing attorney for seven years and 
taught public law at Copenhagen University. 
  In 1974, he moved to Brussels where for three years he 
served 
as an adviser within the European Commission's legal department. 
In 1977-1980 he was deputy cabinet head for Danish Commissioner 
Finn Gundelach. In 1980, Peter Baumann returned to the Danish 
Agriculture Ministry. After six years as office chief, he 
served as a commissioner within the Ministry for three years 
before becoming head of department in 1990. 

</TEXT>

